</p></bio><ref-list><ref id="ref1"><label>1</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Fischer</surname><given-names>Benedikt</given-names></name><name><surname>Rehm</surname><given-names>J&#x000fc;rgen</given-names></name><name><surname>Patra</surname><given-names>Jayadeep</given-names></name><name><surname>Kalousek</surname><given-names>Kate</given-names></name><name><surname>Haydon</surname><given-names>Emma</given-names></name><name><surname>Tyndall</surname><given-names>Mark</given-names></name><name><surname>El-Guebaly</surname><given-names>Nady</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Crack across Canada: Comparing crack users and crack non-users in a Canadian multi-city cohort of illicit opioid users</article-title><source>Addiction</source><year>2006</year><volume>101</volume><issue>12</issue><fpage>1760</fpage><lpage>1770</lpage><comment><ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://doi.wiley.com/10.1111/j.1360-0443.2006.01614.x">http://doi.wiley.com/10.1111/j.1360-0443.2006.01614.x</ext-link></comment><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1111/j.1360-0443.2006.01614.x</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">17156175</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="ref2"><label>2</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Reuter</surname><given-names>Peter</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Why does research have so little impact on American drug policy?</article-title><source>Addiction</source><year>2001</year><volume>96</volume><issue>3</issue><fpage>373</fpage><lpage>376</lpage><comment><ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://doi.wiley.com/10.1046/j.1360-0443.2001.9633731.x">http://doi.wiley.com/10.1046/j.1360-0443.2001.9633731.x</ext-link></comment><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1080/0965214002005437</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">11255577</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="ref3"><label>3</label><elem